s:1349:"<h2>What are row styles?</h2>
<p>Row styles allow the user to change the background of an entire row of modules.</p>
<p>There are typically a selection of row styles available in each template that have a relation to the primary and secondary colours specified in the template.</p>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/row-styles/primary-secondary.png" alt="Priamry and Secondary" /></p>
<h2>Where do you set the row style?</h2>
<p>The row style is applied to a row of modules grouped by their respective rows in the theme panel of the template.</p>
<p>The rows refer to the following module groupings.</p>
<ul>
<li>Top row - top1,top2,top3,top4</li>
<li>Banner row - banner</li>
<li>Grid1 row - grid1,grid2,grid3,grid4</li>
<li>Grid2 row - grid5,grid6,grid7,grid8</li>
<li>Grid3 row - grid9,grid10,grid11,grid12</li>
<li>Grid4 row - grid13,grid14,grid15,grid16</li>
<li>Grid5 row - grid17,grid18,grid19,grid20</li>
<li>Grid6 row - grid21,grid22,grid23,grid24</li>
<li>Bottom row - bottom1,bottom2,bottom3,bottom4,bottom5,bottom6</li>
<li>Top row - top1,top2,top3,top4</li>
</ul>
